gmd:description.gco:CharacterString:
All  NUTS 2006 feature classes were based on common repository coverages. These are collections of geometry from different sources which contain all geometry necessary to created the different feature classes for the datasets COMM, NUTS, CNTR and COAS. The creation of the common repository coverage is a complex process with a lot of manual handling. Such a common repository was created on the 1/100 000 scale level including geometry for the communes (COMM_100K+). This dataset COMM_100K+ served as a based for the lower scale levels of the NUTS, CNTR and COAS datasets:
A: From this COMM_100K+ a new common repository for the NUTS 2006 (NUTS_2006+) on a 100K scale was derived (dissolved operation);
B: This NUTS_2006+ (100K) was generalized on the scale levels 1M, 3M, 10M, 20M and 60M;
C: From these scale levels of the NUTS_2006+ all lower scale feature classes of CNTR, COAS and NUTS were derived. This derivation included following steps:
	(i) Apply boundary coding procedure on all scales of NUTS_2006+;
	(ii) Derive CNTR feature classes on all scale levels
	(iii) Derive COAS feature classes on all scale levels
	(iv) Derive NUTS feature classes on all scale levels
	(v) Remove pseudonodes from arcs
	(vi) Create info table with arc-polygon relationship for all scales
